@startuml
title OpenIPC Motors - Control Flow Sequence Diagram

actor "Camera Application" as App
participant "Motors Daemon" as Daemon
participant "Driver Wrapper" as Wrapper
participant "Kernel Driver\n(Optional)" as Kernel
participant "Hardware Interface\n(GPIO/I2C/SPI/UART)" as Hardware
participant "Motor Controller\nHardware" as Motor

== Initialization Phase ==
App -> Daemon: Connect via Unix Socket
activate Daemon
Daemon -> Daemon: Load Configuration\n(GPIO pins, max steps)
Daemon -> Wrapper: Initialize Driver Wrapper
activate Wrapper
Wrapper -> Kernel: Open Device (/dev/motor)
activate Kernel
Kernel -> Hardware: Initialize Hardware Interface\n(GPIO/I2C/SPI/UART)
activate Hardware
Hardware -> Motor: Send Initialization Sequence
activate Motor
Motor --> Hardware: ACK
Hardware --> Kernel: Success
Kernel --> Wrapper: Device Ready
Wrapper --> Daemon: Driver Initialized
deactivate Kernel
deactivate Wrapper
Daemon --> App: Connection Established
deactivate Daemon

== Motor Control Command Flow ==
App -> Daemon: Send Motor Command\n(Pan/Tilt/Zoom/Focus + Speed)
activate Daemon
Daemon -> Daemon: Validate Command Parameters
Daemon -> Wrapper: Translate to Driver-Specific Command
activate Wrapper

alt GPIO-based Control (camhi-motor/ingenic-motor)
    Wrapper -> Kernel: ioctl() with Motor Command
    activate Kernel
    Kernel -> Hardware: Set GPIO Pins
    Hardware -> Motor: Direct GPIO Control Signal
    Motor -> Motor: Execute Movement
    Motor --> Hardware: Position Update
    Hardware --> Kernel: GPIO State
    Kernel --> Wrapper: Command Executed
    deactivate Kernel
else I2C-based Control (i2c-motor)
    Wrapper -> Hardware: I2C Write Command\n(via i2c-dev.h)
    Hardware -> Motor: I2C Motor Driver Command
    Motor -> Motor: Execute Movement
    Motor --> Hardware: I2C Response
    Hardware --> Wrapper: Command Executed
else SPI-based Control (AN41908A)
    Wrapper -> Hardware: SPI Command Sequence
    Hardware -> Motor: AN41908A Control Signal
    Motor -> Motor: Execute Movement\n(Focus/Zoom/Iris)
    Motor --> Hardware: SPI Response
    Hardware --> Wrapper: Command Executed
else UART-based Control (Pelco-D)
    Wrapper -> Hardware: Serial Write\n(Pelco-D Protocol Packet)
    Hardware -> Motor: UART PTZ Command
    Motor -> Motor: Execute PTZ Movement
    Motor --> Hardware: Status (if supported)
    Hardware --> Wrapper: Command Executed
end

Wrapper --> Daemon: Execution Status
deactivate Wrapper
Daemon --> App: Command Result
deactivate Daemon

== Status Query Flow ==
App -> Daemon: Query Motor Status
activate Daemon
Daemon -> Wrapper: Get Status Request
activate Wrapper
Wrapper -> Kernel: ioctl() Read Status
activate Kernel
Kernel -> Hardware: Read Hardware State
activate Hardware
Hardware -> Motor: Query Position/Limits
Motor --> Hardware: Current State
deactivate Hardware
Hardware --> Kernel: Status Data
Kernel --> Wrapper: Motor Position & Limits
deactivate Kernel
Wrapper -> Wrapper: Format Status\n(JSON output)
Wrapper --> Daemon: Structured Status Data
deactivate Wrapper
Daemon --> App: Status Response\n(Position, Limits)
deactivate Daemon

== Autofocus Flow ==
App -> Daemon: Trigger Autofocus
activate Daemon
Daemon -> Wrapper: Start Autofocus Routine
activate Wrapper
loop Focus Search Algorithm
    Wrapper -> Kernel: ioctl() Focus Command
    activate Kernel
    Kernel -> Hardware: Set Focus Position
    Hardware -> Motor: Adjust Focus
    Motor --> Hardware: Position Reached
    deactivate Hardware
    Hardware --> Kernel: Complete
    Kernel --> Wrapper: Position Set
    deactivate Kernel
    Wrapper -> App: Request Image Sharpness\n(via callback/API)
    App --> Wrapper: Sharpness Metric
    Wrapper -> Wrapper: Evaluate Focus Quality
end
Wrapper -> Wrapper: Optimal Focus Found
Wrapper --> Daemon: Autofocus Complete
deactivate Wrapper
Daemon --> App: Focus Locked
deactivate Daemon

== Shutdown Phase ==
App -> Daemon: Disconnect Request
activate Daemon
Daemon -> Wrapper: Shutdown Driver
activate Wrapper
Wrapper -> Kernel: Close Device
activate Kernel
Kernel -> Hardware: Release Hardware Interface
activate Hardware
Hardware -> Motor: Stop All Movement
Motor --> Hardware: Motors Stopped
Hardware --> Kernel: Released
deactivate Hardware
Kernel --> Wrapper: Device Closed
deactivate Kernel
Wrapper --> Daemon: Driver Stopped
deactivate Wrapper
Daemon --> App: Disconnected
deactivate Daemon

@enduml
